This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the problem of similarity search over chemical compound databases. It also involves the use of indexing structures for efficient searching, which is a common topic in IR. 

It could also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category as it deals with the organization and retrieval of data from a large database of chemical compounds. 

The paper's use of efficient indexing structures and data structures suggests it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper's focus on the discovery and design of novel drug-like molecules suggests it could belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category.
